# VI, VIM EDITORS MODES

• Command Mode - Press Esc (Default Mode)

• Insert Mode - Press i, I, a, A, o, O

• Ex Mode (Execution Mode / Escape Mode) - Press : (Shift + ;)

---

# COMMAND MODE

Default mode of vi editor.

In this mode we can:

* Copy text
* Paste text
* Delete text
* Search text
* Navigate within the file

## Copy Commands

yy      --> Copy current line

3yy     --> Copy 3 lines from current cursor position

## Paste Commands

p       --> Paste copied content below the cursor

P       --> Paste copied content above the cursor

4p      --> Paste copied content 4 times

## Delete Commands

dd      --> Delete (cut) current line

4dd     --> Delete (cut) 4 lines

## Navigation Commands

G       --> Move cursor to end of file

gg      --> Move cursor to beginning of file

## Search Commands

/word   --> Search forward for a word

?word   --> Search backward for a word

n       --> Next search result

N       --> Previous search result

## Undo / Redo

u        --> Undo last change

Ctrl + r --> Redo last undone change

---

# CURSOR MOVEMENT IN COMMAND MODE

h j k l

h --> Move cursor left

j --> Move cursor down

k --> Move cursor up

l --> Move cursor right

---


# INSERT MODE

Used to add or modify file contents.

Switch from Command Mode to Insert Mode using:

i --> Insert text before current cursor position

I --> Insert text at beginning of current line

a --> Add text after current cursor position

A --> Add text at end of current line

o --> Open a new line below current cursor position

O --> Open a new line above current cursor position

---

# EX MODE (EXTENDED COMMAND MODE)

Press : (Shift + ;) to enter Ex Mode.

## Quit Commands

:q      --> Quit file

:q!     --> Force quit without saving

## Save Commands

:w      --> Save changes

:w!     --> Force save changes

## Save and Quit Commands

:wq     --> Save and quit

:wq!    --> Force save and quit

:x      --> Save and quit

## Encryption

:X      --> Encrypt file contents

## Line Navigation

:25     --> Move cursor to line number 25

## Line Numbers

:set nu     --> Display line numbers

:set nonu   --> Remove line numbers

## Delete Specific Line

:5d     --> Delete line number 5

